title: 'No Rust protection.'
body: Hi, I purchased this to fix small issues around my house, and this is honestly the worst purchase I have ever made. The tools got wet after fixing some plumbing-related issues (just a few drops here and there). I left the took kit open, assuming the water would dry off as it's just small drops. But to my surprise, the tools had rust forming on them the next morning.  I understand if rust builds up after a few days in moisture, but this happened within 1 week of purchase. I don't know if there's a better kit, but you should not waste your money here.

column15: which makes it easy to carry around and store. The tools are housed in a sturdy and durable case
column16: which not only protects them from damage but also keeps them organized.  In terms of price

column18: making it an excellent value for money. Compared to other products in the same price range
